Here are the user stories derived from the Python code:

As a data manager, I want to process data deletions for a specific date, so that outdated or sensitive data is removed efficiently.  
As a UI designer, I want to redesign a specific page, so that it matches new design styles.  
As a UI designer, I want to report user testing results to agencies, so that feedback is documented and addressed.  
As a UI designer, I want to move to the next round of edits for approval, so that leadership can review changes.  
As a UI designer, I want to track issues from testing sessions, so that problems can be resolved in future iterations.  
As a UI designer, I want to schedule user testing with advanced notice, so that participants are prepared and available.  
As a developer, I want to enhance logging for a specific submission, so that debugging is more effective.  
As a developer, I want to update the publish status of a submission, so that the system reflects the latest state.  
As a developer, I want to update validation rules in the database, so that data integrity is maintained.  
As a developer, I want to add GTAS window data to the database, so that the system has the latest information.  
As a developer, I want to manage and cache D Files generation requests, so that performance is optimized.  
As a DevOps engineer, I want to configure New Relic for applications, so that monitoring is enabled.  
As a DevOps engineer, I want to reset environment permissions, so that security policies are enforced.  
As a Broker user, I want to update upload and validate error messages, so that users receive clear feedback.  
As a Broker user, I want to sync D1 file generation with FPDS data load, so that data is consistent.  
As a Broker user, I want to create content mockups for submissions, so that designs are reviewed before implementation.  
As a website user, I want to access published files of a specific type, so that I can retrieve needed documents.  
As an agency user, I want to include flexfields with optimization, so that forms are customizable and performant.  
As an agency user, I want to validate flexfields for submissions, so that data meets requirements.  
As an owner, I want to create a user testing summary, so that results are documented for stakeholders.  
As an owner, I want to design a timeline for UI improvements, so that progress is tracked.  
As an owner, I want to design an audit for UI improvements, so that changes are validated.  
As a FABS user, I want to deactivate the publish button during derivations, so that accidental submissions are prevented.  
As a FABS user, I want to download uploaded FABS files, so that I can access submitted data.  
As a data user, I want to receive updates to FABS records, so that I have the latest information.  
As a tester, I want to access test features in a specific environment, so that I can verify functionality.
